        <font color="midnightblue" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="2"> I have a question. Has anyone ever had an instance where they gave a weapon to an enchanter, and they give you the cost, you give them the item and when you get it back it is the same. </P><P>I had this happen to me on 2 different occasions. The first was a drop helm and it cost me 2 gold and gave me nothing. Later I discovered that only player created items can be enchanted. So, Phy made a sword for me and as good as it was I needed a little extra 16 ounces of Whoop A$$ on it. I took it to the enchantress in Ardribards and she said it would be 4 gold 70 silver. I payed her she said the work was complete. I got the item back, the gold was gone and no extra properties whatsoever. What up wit' dat?</P><P>The gold was basically a gimme since my benefactor (Phyleus) not only made the weapon, he gave me the cash to upgrade it. Any info from my brothers and sisters would be welcome.</P><P>Voltan Hawkslayer<BR>"Slayer for the Church of Albion"</P><P></font></td>

