        <hr noshade size="1">
        
        <font color="midnightblue" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="2"> Actually, recent testing has shown that enchanting <B>DOES</B> improve the damage output of a given weapon. A very large difference actually, so much so that the 98%QUA+ player crafted 35% bonus stuff is FAR superior to anything else in the game, even items with skill increases, stat bonuses and procs. But with Sanya telling people that bonus only affects to-hit modifiers, people aren't going to fork out cash for player-crafted as they will think it is worse.</P><P>When I get to within usability of Arcanium weapons there is no way I'm not going with player crafted all the way. 35% bonus is yummy <img src=icon_smile.gif border=0 align=middle></P><P>AC Lord of Adventure<BR>SB Bishop of the Apostles of Loromir<BR>DAoC : Greggar McDougal - Justicator of the Church<a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height=15 width=15 border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
